<section
  id='case-lumastays'
  class='fullscreen-section'
  data-title='Case Study: Luma Stays — Web Development | Katja Turnsek'
  data-description='React accommodation booking case study focused on API integration, authentication, routing, booking flows, profile management, and role-based functionality.'
  data-case='lumastays'
>
  <div class='rows'>
    <div class='row'>
      <h1>Web Development</h1>
      <h2>Luma Stays - Accommodation Booking App</h2>

      <div class='tech-demo-wrapper'>
        <div class='tech-stack'><strong>Tools:</strong>
          React | JavaScript | Bootstrap | Noroff API</div>

        <div class='demo-links' data-auto='demo' data-case='lumastays'></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <nav
        class='project-switcher'
        aria-label='Luma Stays sections'
        data-auto='switcher'
        data-case='lumastays'
      ></nav>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Objective</h3>
      <p>
        To build a complete
        <strong>accommodation booking application</strong>
        with venue browsing, search, detailed venue pages, booking functionality, profile
        management, and manager tools. The focus was to create a structured front-end app that
        handles real API data while keeping the user journey clear from browsing to booking.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <div class='case-study-columns'>
        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <div class='case-study-text'>
            <h3>Development Focus</h3>
            <ul class='bullet-list'>
              <li>
                Built as a
                <strong>React single-page application</strong>
                with routed views, reusable components, and clear page structure
              </li>
              <li>
                Integrated the
                <strong>Noroff Holidaze API</strong>
                for venues, profiles, bookings, authentication, and manager-specific data
              </li>
              <li>
                Developed
                <strong>customer and venue manager flows</strong>
                with different available actions depending on the user role
              </li>
              <li>
                Used
                <strong>Bootstrap with custom CSS</strong>
                to create a responsive interface that still feels branded and polished
              </li>
              <li>
                Focused on
                <strong>stable UI states</strong>
                for loading, errors, forms, image handling, bookings, and profile updates
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <figure class='case-study-item item-right'>
            <img
              class='thumb'
              src='{{base}}assets/images/site-lumastays-600.webp'
              data-src='site-lumastays-600.webp'
              data-path='assets/images'
              alt='Luma Stays explore page showing accommodation cards, search, and filter interface'
            />
            <figcaption class='work-caption'>Desktop version - Explore stays</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <figure class='case-study-item item-left'>
            <img
              class='thumb'
              src='{{base}}assets/images/web-lumastays-booking-600.webp'
              data-src='web-lumastays-booking-600.webp'
              data-path='assets/images'
              alt='Luma Stays venue detail page showing booking options and guest selection'
            />
            <figcaption class='work-caption'>Desktop version - Venue details and booking</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <div class='case-study-wrapper'>
          <div class='case-study-text'>
            <h3>Key Features</h3>
            <ul class='bullet-list-right'>
              <li>
                <strong>Venue browsing</strong>
                with responsive cards, search, filtering, pricing, and clear venue information
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Venue detail pages</strong>
                with images, facilities, descriptions, pricing, and booking actions
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Booking flow</strong>
                for logged-in customers, including guest selection and booking feedback
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Profile area</strong>
                where users can view bookings, update their avatar, and manage account details
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Manager functionality</strong>
                for creating, editing, and managing accommodation listings
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='row'>
      <h3>Reflection</h3>
      <p>
        Luma Stays is one of my strongest front-end projects because it brings together
        <strong>React, API integration, authentication, routing, forms, booking logic, and
          role-based user flows</strong>
        in one complete application. It strengthened how I structure larger apps, work with changing
        API data, and design functionality that supports different user needs without making the
        interface feel complicated.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class='back-to-work-container'>
      <a
        href='{{base}}#work'
        class='label-link back-to-work-label'
        data-back
        data-back-fallback='{{base}}#work'
        aria-label='Go back'
      >
        <svg class='icon icon-18 arrow-icon' aria-hidden='true'><use href='#i-arrow-left' /></svg>
        <span class='label-text'>Back to Work</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>